10:
When a lady says no, you should
really listen. Little Cub, it's safe to
come out—
41:
I'm sorry. We should've been long
gone by now...
45:
There's no need to push yourself.
Rest a little longer, okay?
47:
If it helps, you should know that I'm
not the only one looking out for you.
Whitetail is on his way as well.
56:
Indeed. Him and a few other
companions. They're an odd bunch.
59:
But they've proven to be reliable
allies time and again. Unlike myself.
67:
I know what I am—a warrior who has
committed enough crimes and sins
for a lifetime.
70:
But at the very least, I can serve as
your shield.
81: How are you able to laugh like that?
84: You said you did bad things.
86:
My mom... she told me the lionfolk
did a really bad thing a long time
ago.
89: We don't deserve the right to laugh—
96:
One day, the home I've found will be
gone. I understand this.
99:
However, I've resolved to keep a
smile despite it all. At least until the
very end.
103: Isn't that... a painful way to live?
112: But it'll be all right. You are—
118: Shuilong?! What are you doing here?
125:
We're staying with the same people,
so I've seen her around town...
128:
Shuilong, who are you contracted to
now?
133:
Boy, Magnos is looking for you. Don't
keep him waiting.
137: Little Cub, make a run for it!
141: You want to get in the way?
174:
I suppose this is the best a child can
do.
178: You didn't kill him, did you?
183:
What, did you think I'd go back on
our contract?
187: Grab the boy and the woman.
